It also says that no earthly nation can claim any political<br>
jurisdiction in space  beyond the earth it self. This means that every space colony must be totally independant from the earth politicly from the beginning of its existance, and must<br>
be an independant nation state , whose people own all its resources. This separates the fate of our space colonies from that of the earth. This is in the best interest of mankind because we should not be surprised to see Ray Bradbarys<br>
martian chronicles become reality someday. We should not be surprised to see the earth blow itself up in a nuclear war in the future. Then the civilization of the martian colonists of the future will outlive the civilization of the earth , and it will ultimately repopulate the earth , expand to the outer solar system and colonize the nearby stars . This will be the next great step in the evolution of mankind to a higher level. <br>
The inferior, stupid, backward, primitive, ignorant and corrupt  present global human civilization  of the earth and its people will then  pass into  history and then perhaps the human civilization of mars will become true martians,and will develop a superior human civilization, and a superior branch of the human race . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1038<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/29/02 10:41:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=186.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~projectorion/ezboard/posticons/12.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The outer space treaty, and space colonies</span><hr size=1> Like the Lunar treaty these papers have been mostly ignored. I think only 4 nations ratified one of those treaties and all the spacefaring nations except France snubbed them entirely. When tested these ill thought out partially signed agreements will be totally ignored. They will probably be amended once France decides to take a slice of the space resource pie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orion Commander</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/30/02 6:34:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=186.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><t